ith Alex Belth</a></span><span> </span></p><blockquote style=3D"border-left=
: 4px solid #FF7731;margin: 20px 0;padding: 0;"><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20p=
x 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16p=
x;">We left the Bronx and moved to a small village in Vermont, grateful to =
be safe and in less clamorous environs. Emily appreciated the change&#8212;=
and in time, so did I&#8212;but her health didn&#8217;t miraculously improv=
e. Her visual system, in particular, continued to decline. Watching TV for =
more than a minute made her ill&#8212;she had to limit time on the phone, a=
nd good luck with that&#8212;let alone looking at a computer, or through th=
e windshield of my car.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,=
55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">There&#8217;s onl=
y so many hours one can listen to podcasts on the couch without going mad. =
So one evening five years ago just before Thanksgiving, Em says to me, &#82=
20;Let&#8217;s paint.&#8221;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(5=
4,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">I smiled. Sh=
e didn&#8217;t like drawing or painting even though her mother is a fabulou=
s visual artist. (I took Em to the Metropolitan Museum of Art on our first =
date, thinking I&#8217;d impress her with my knowledge of painting; I talke=
d until I left her limp. And hungry.)</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;col=
or: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">&#8=
220;Of course,&#8221; I said, &#8220;love to join you.&#8221;</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: =
26px;font-size: 16px;">We set ourselves up on the dining room table with ac=
rylics and markers. She made abstract pictures, interrupting herself only t=
o tell me she didn&#8217;t know what she was doing.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-si=
ze: 16px;">I drew pictures of her.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color:=
 rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Em&#82=
17;s artistic career was short-lived. After a few days, the painting fucked=
 up her vision just like everything else. By that point, I was in a groove.=
 And so during the first long covid winter, I made drawings and paintings o=
f my wife and it was like seeing her for the first time.</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;fo=
nt-size: 16px;">It would take time to knock the rust off my skills, but I w=
asn&#8217;t crippled by self-doubt and criticism.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 =
0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size=
: 16px;">There are few pieces of writing I look back on with affection, but=
 I dig my artwork, despite the technical flaws. Experiencing this again was=
 unexpected, surprising and energizing.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;c=
olor: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">D=
rawing someone, capturing not so much their likeness but their spirit, is t=
he stuff of infatuation; it took on a different energy with someone I&#8217=
;d known, and adored, for almost twenty years.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 2=
0px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 1=
6px;">I drew Em as we hung out in the evenings, occasionally asking her to =
hold still a sec, but just as often working from photographs I&#8217;d take=
n with my phone. After finishing a picture, which could take minutes or day=
s, I showed it to her, half-eager for her approval while anxious to be free=
 of wanting it. (No wonder uncle Fred didn&#8217;t fill in facial features&=
#8212;they weren&#8217;t only difficult to render but tempting to over-work=
=2E)</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;c=
olor: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px=
;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Em usually brightened at the sight of =
them, the colors, the vibe, and liked some and didn&#8217;t like others.</p=
><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line=
-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">&#8220;I&#8217;ve never been anyone&#8217;s=
 muse,&#8221; she said.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,=
55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">I&#8217;ve watche=
d her a lot over the years, suffering and in despair. I&#8217;ve watched he=
r sleep, her features soft and unguarded while I pray for relief. And I&#82=
17;ve watched her doubled over in laughter after calling me a cheater and a=
 slut for beating her in a game of backgammon.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 2=
0px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 1=
6px;">Over the course of three years I made hundreds of drawings and dozens=
 of paintings of my wife, evoking her many moods&#8212;and mine.</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height:=
 26px;font-size: 16px;">We worried about how best to hang all this artwork =
in the living room. When I asked our landlord for advice, he didn&#8217;t w=
arn me about making holes in the walls. Instead, he said: &#8220;Perfection=
 is an offense to the gods!&#8221;</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color:=
 rgb(54,55,55);margin-left: 20px;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">A haph=
azard gallery of more than 20 picture frames went up&#8212;11x8 drawings, 1=
8x24 paintings. Sometimes, I&#8217;d be so excited to finish a painting ses=
sion just to get the canvas on the wall.</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
